      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Very even with a host of win chances. BUZZAROON (2) is worth another chance back at home. Was close-up fresh then raced a little one paced second-up over a mile at Ballarat. Fitter and slightly longer trip a plus. Down in weight and well worth another chance. REVOLVER (4) is another coming off a below par run. Winner two back then safely held at Sandown Hillside latest. This easier and gets chance to atone. FEARGAL (5) is close to breaking through after finishing third last start over 1800m at Hanging Rock when he was prominent throughout. Has strung together some good run and deserves a win. WICHITALL (1) on the other hand has been in great winning form scoring back to back wins across the border. Has the claim and can run well again. OTTELIA (8) is a progressive mare showing ability and can measure up over the longer journey.",
